I see - the client methods call `getFeedResponse` with the URL from `service.feeds.getValue(FeedType.X)`. The MockEngine resolves these URLs against the filesystem. For bcycle, I notice it doesn't have a `system_hours.json` file, but the bcycle test doesn't call `getSystemHours()` so that's fine.

Wait, let me look at what the bcycle test actually calls:
```kotlin
context(service) {
  assertTrue(client.getSystemInformation().isSuccess)
  assertTrue(client.getStationInformation().isSuccess)
  assertTrue(client.getStationStatus().isSuccess)
